section.t:
The benefit of using an UMA authorization server, requesting party tokens, and so on to manage Alice's control of her doctor's and others' access to the data her scale generates is that she:  
does not have to be present when they request access, crafting policies prior to access attempts or handling access approval requests after attempts;
can demand that requesting parties present proof of their suitability (such as current valid hospital credentials);
can change the length permission validity, including revoking sharing relationships; 
can set policies governing clients used by requesting parties as well; and 
can do this from a centralizable authorization point, crossing multiple resource servers (and thus devices feeding into them).
